WEBVTT

00:18.810 --> 00:20.072
MAN:
Yo, watch out.

00:36.270 --> 00:38.261
First Street and Second Avenue.

01:38.860 --> 01:40.725
Very dangerous,
Afghanistan.

01:40.760 --> 01:42.227
Is that why you left?

01:42.270 --> 01:44.795
I have family, uh...

01:44.830 --> 01:46.058
young children.

01:46.100 --> 01:49.831
But many men would still welcome
the chance to become a martyr.

01:59.780 --> 02:01.919
LEBOWITZ: Detective Wells,
your testimony

02:01.950 --> 02:05.181
is that, while acting as an
undercover police officer,

02:05.220 --> 02:07.359
you allegedly purchased
illegal narcotics

02:07.390 --> 02:08.914
from my client.
Is that right?
Yes.

02:08.960 --> 02:11.827
And you've recalled
those conversations here today

02:11.860 --> 02:13.851
in rather astonishing detail.

02:13.900 --> 02:15.697
Haven't you?
Word for word.

02:17.200 --> 02:18.497
Word for word?

02:20.540 --> 02:21.438
Yeah.

02:21.470 --> 02:24.564
Conversations that occurred
over a year ago.

02:24.610 --> 02:26.931
October 22, 2011.

02:26.980 --> 02:28.504
It was a Saturday.

02:28.540 --> 02:30.770
Between 2:44 and 3:16
at Suriyo Thai

02:30.810 --> 02:32.744
in Kew Gardens.
And then again,
two days later,

02:32.780 --> 02:34.213
in your client's hotel room,

02:34.250 --> 02:36.548
between 6:46 and 7:17,

02:36.590 --> 02:38.842
when he tried
to sell me the drugs.

02:38.890 --> 02:40.482
What, exactly,
did you use

02:40.520 --> 02:42.624
to refresh your recollection
of those conversations?

02:42.660 --> 02:44.685
My recollections
don't need refreshing.

02:44.730 --> 02:45.856
So... what,

02:45.890 --> 02:47.949
you just... remember them?
Yeah.

02:48.000 --> 02:49.888
I remember everything.

02:49.930 --> 02:51.625
LEBOWITZ:
Everything?
CARRIE:
Yeah.

02:51.670 --> 02:52.694
Everything.

02:52.740 --> 02:55.231
I'm sure you do, Detective.

02:55.270 --> 02:57.261
No further questions,
Your Honor.

02:58.540 --> 03:00.303
Your Honor,
if you'll indulge me

03:00.340 --> 03:01.602
for a moment?

03:02.710 --> 03:03.938
PROSECUTOR:
Detective, where were you

03:03.980 --> 03:05.174
at 2:47 last Friday afternoon?

03:05.210 --> 03:07.770
Walking across the plaza out
front of the courthouse here.

03:07.820 --> 03:09.481
Did you, at that time,
recognize anyone

03:09.520 --> 03:10.987
who is presently
in this courtroom?

03:11.020 --> 03:13.887
Yes. Mr. Lebowitz over there,
and juror number seven,

03:13.920 --> 03:16.889
front row,
second from the end.

03:16.930 --> 03:18.989
Do you recall
what they were doing?

03:19.030 --> 03:20.895
Yeah, Mr. Lebowitz
was ordering souvlaki,

03:20.930 --> 03:23.728
no peppers, extra onions,

03:23.770 --> 03:25.897
and coconut milk, with pulp.

03:25.930 --> 03:27.864
And juror number seven
was talking to a very pretty

03:27.900 --> 03:29.367
young blonde woman.

03:29.410 --> 03:30.900
Your Honor, you can't allow...

03:30.940 --> 03:31.804
Easy, Lebowitz.

03:31.840 --> 03:33.979
Did you have souvlaki
last Friday or not?

03:34.010 --> 03:36.342
I-I don't really...

03:36.380 --> 03:37.449
Remember?

03:37.480 --> 03:38.879
PROSECUTOR:
What was juror seven

03:38.910 --> 03:40.719
wearing at that time,
Detective Wells?

03:40.750 --> 03:42.012
Brown pantsuit,

03:42.050 --> 03:43.813
cream blouse, Tory Birch flats,

03:43.850 --> 03:46.387
and a beige silk scarf.
You looked very nice.

03:46.420 --> 03:48.650
And the young woman
she was with?
Navy blue cardigan,

03:48.690 --> 03:49.827
six buttons down the front,

03:49.860 --> 03:52.021
white slacks, black flats,

03:52.060 --> 03:54.255
a Prada purse, black Tessuto...

03:54.300 --> 03:55.551
a knockoff.

03:55.600 --> 03:56.999
I'm sorry, you can tell

03:57.030 --> 03:59.430
by the clasp.
Oh, my daughter--

03:59.470 --> 04:00.994
I toldher it was fake.

04:01.040 --> 04:03.964
Anything else, Mr. Lebowitz?

04:11.310 --> 04:13.540
How'd it go?
Oh, walk in the park.

04:13.580 --> 04:15.719
I'm starting to feel bad
for these defense attorneys.

04:15.750 --> 04:17.547
And not the
rest of us?
Hm.

04:17.590 --> 04:19.581
Bashir Sajadi,
42,cabdnven

04:19.620 --> 04:20.985
Took a bullet
in the back.

04:21.020 --> 04:22.521
These two gentlemen

04:22.560 --> 04:23.982
are the ones who found him.

04:24.030 --> 04:25.850
What's he doing here?

04:25.890 --> 04:28.393
AL: Commissioner's Office
has eyes on this one.

04:28.430 --> 04:30.898
Carrie. Al.
How'd you get all the way
to Brooklyn, Eliot?

04:30.930 --> 04:32.932
And please tell me
it wasn't in that cab.

04:32.970 --> 04:35.894
I came with the Commissioner's
Joint Task Force.

04:35.940 --> 04:38.408
Turns out our victim
was one of their Informants.

04:38.440 --> 04:40.328
Sajadi was cooperating
in an investigation

04:40.380 --> 04:43.042
of a radical mosque.
_ A terrorist
Investigation.

04:43.080 --> 04:44.638
Now that they have
a high-profile homicide

04:44.680 --> 04:46.477
on their hands,
they called in Major Crimes.

04:46.520 --> 04:48.545
Theory is that the two targets
of the investigation

04:48.580 --> 04:51.583
somehow made Sajadi as a rat
and took him out.

04:51.620 --> 04:55.351
So where are the targets now?
JTF's trying to get eyes
on them as we speak.

04:55.390 --> 04:57.426
Trying to get
eyes on them?
Easy, Sparky.

04:57.460 --> 04:59.849
This is one _of over a_ dozen
active terrorist investigations

04:59.900 --> 05:01.822
they're running--
you can't expect them to have

05:01.860 --> 05:03.020
24/7 surveillance

05:03.070 --> 05:06.938
on all of them.
Yeah, well, tell that
to Bashir Sajadi.

05:08.940 --> 05:10.737
Trunk was open,

05:10.770 --> 05:12.579
but nothing's missing.

05:12.610 --> 05:14.771
Wallet, cell phone--
all here.

05:15.940 --> 05:18.340
No blood in the cab, either.

05:18.380 --> 05:22.783
Looks like they just pulled
him out and executed him.

05:24.920 --> 05:27.582
AL:
Not a place I'd choose

05:27.620 --> 05:28.780
to whack someone.

05:31.090 --> 05:33.627
Anybody could've made him.

05:34.730 --> 05:37.062
Well, whatever
they were planning...

05:37.100 --> 05:39.796
it was worth the risk.

05:54.650 --> 05:56.447
JAY: Man on the left
is Farhan Hazara.

05:56.490 --> 05:58.788
One on the right
is Babur Rashad.

05:58.820 --> 06:00.117
Hazara's an Afghan national;

06:00.160 --> 06:01.912
Rashad is strictly homegrown,
born in New Jersey.

06:01.960 --> 06:02.949
If the guy's
a suspected terrorist,

06:02.990 --> 06:04.082
how'd he get a work visa?

06:04.130 --> 06:05.722
It's all about
who you know, right?

06:05.760 --> 06:07.796
Rashad worked
with Coalition forces

06:07.830 --> 06:08.854
as a civilian interpreter.

06:08.900 --> 06:11.528
He's currently assigned
to the UN.

06:11.570 --> 06:13.561
What exactly were
they being investigated for?

06:13.600 --> 06:15.465
I reached out
to an FBI agent

06:15.500 --> 06:17.161
who's on the terrorism
task force-- he says

06:17.210 --> 06:19.906
both were suspects
in a potential weapons purchase.

06:19.940 --> 06:23.444
The idea was to set up a buy,
and then flip the two targets

06:23.480 --> 06:24.902
and move higher
up the food chain.

06:24.950 --> 06:26.542
How does our cabdriver fit in?

06:26.580 --> 06:28.810
Rashad and Hazara both
attend mosque in Brooklyn.

06:28.850 --> 06:30.738
The task force believes
the mosque was a source of money

06:30.790 --> 06:32.678
for the weapons buy.
Our cabdriver was flagged

06:32.720 --> 06:35.518
as a potential asset when
he applied for his green card.

06:35.560 --> 06:36.754
Basically,
he was told his application

06:36.790 --> 06:39.122
would be fast-tracked if he
agreed to infiltrate the mosque.

06:39.160 --> 06:41.799
The problem is, we got nothing
to link either of them to this.

06:41.830 --> 06:44.094
How about a dead cabbie who
just happened to be informing

06:44.130 --> 06:45.961
against them--
there's your link.
It's motive, yes.

06:46.000 --> 06:47.035
We're gonna need more.

06:47.070 --> 06:48.264
So let's get more.
The task force

06:48.300 --> 06:51.007
has eyes on both these guys now;
they're not going anywhere.

06:51.040 --> 06:53.031
In the meantime, we work
the case through forensics

06:53.080 --> 06:55.401
and witnesses just like
any other, right?

06:56.580 --> 07:00.118
Guy offers to help his new
country, takes a bullet for it.

07:03.690 --> 07:05.646
AL:
According to Sajadi's

07:05.690 --> 07:08.750
ride log, his last fare was
a pickup here on Broadway,

07:08.790 --> 07:12.556
between 73rd and 74th.

07:13.560 --> 07:16.051
No traffic cams-- but
look for other video.

07:16.100 --> 07:17.567
All right.

07:17.600 --> 07:19.227
Let's say it was
the two terrorists--

07:19.270 --> 07:22.194
what are they doing up here?

07:22.240 --> 07:24.959
I mean, think about it,
there's no obvious targets,

07:25.010 --> 07:27.570
landmarks, symbols
of New York, nothing.
Are you kidding?

07:27.610 --> 07:29.601
There's a Mango Dog on 7lst.

07:29.650 --> 07:31.504
Mango Dog is New York.

07:31.550 --> 07:32.619
They should use that.

07:32.650 --> 07:35.619
Busy subway station at 72nd.

07:35.650 --> 07:37.242
You could do
a lot of damage

07:37.290 --> 07:39.212
with a couple of assault rifles.

07:39.250 --> 07:40.217
Yeah.

07:40.260 --> 07:41.579
JAY:
Hey, I just got back

07:41.620 --> 07:43.087
a victim's cell phone records.

07:43.130 --> 07:44.586
'2
| And. _
There s an incoming call

07:44.630 --> 07:46.495
about a minute
after he picks up his fare.

07:46.530 --> 07:48.225
We know who it was?

07:48.260 --> 07:50.069
I ran down the number, but it
traced back to a disposable

07:50.100 --> 07:51.829
burner cell--
no name, no address.

07:51.870 --> 07:54.259
AL:
You try calling the number?

07:54.300 --> 07:57.235
Yep. No voicemail, no I.D.

07:57.270 --> 07:58.100
We're checking serial numbers,

07:58.140 --> 08:00.108
trying to find out
where it was sold.

08:00.140 --> 08:01.971
All right, keep on it.

08:03.180 --> 08:05.876
Looks like Sajadi
got a call.

08:05.910 --> 08:08.140
Probably while his killer
was in the cab.

08:08.180 --> 08:10.546
I'm thinking,
they call his cell,

08:10.590 --> 08:11.682
odds are it's someone
that knows him.

08:11.720 --> 08:12.948
What about his wife?

08:12.990 --> 08:15.151
I mean, if Sajadi
knew the caller,

08:15.190 --> 08:17.055
maybe his wife does, too.

08:20.160 --> 08:22.151
He was a good man,

08:22.200 --> 08:24.225
a good father.

08:24.270 --> 08:26.989
I had to get them
out of the house.

08:27.040 --> 08:28.689
Of course.
Bashir would

08:28.740 --> 08:31.538
never get involved
with terrorists.

08:31.570 --> 08:32.537
Hamid!

08:39.580 --> 08:42.617
It's all fixed.

08:46.860 --> 08:49.852
He looks like his father.
Mrs. Sajadi,

08:49.890 --> 08:51.926
we know your husband
was doing nothing wrong.

08:51.960 --> 08:53.996
In fact, he was working
with the police

08:54.030 --> 08:55.327
to prevent a terrorist attack.

08:55.360 --> 08:57.726
Bashir was working
for the police?

08:57.770 --> 08:59.567
He was helping
in an investigation.

08:59.600 --> 09:02.160
Is that why he was killed?
We're not sure.

09:02.200 --> 09:05.101
Ma'am, do you recognize

09:05.140 --> 09:07.131
either of these men?

09:09.210 --> 09:10.438
No. I've never seen them.

09:10.480 --> 09:13.938
I don't understand-- why would
Bashir get involved with this?

09:13.980 --> 09:16.642
Because he was promised
a green card.

09:17.990 --> 09:20.982
He did it so that you
and your kids could
have a chance.

09:21.020 --> 09:22.851
Mrs. Sajadi,

09:22.890 --> 09:26.758
your husband got a phone call
the day he was killed.

09:26.800 --> 09:29.189
Do you know this number?

09:30.230 --> 09:31.822
That's Mo's number.

09:31.870 --> 09:33.098
Mo?

09:33.140 --> 09:34.835
Moshin Aziz,
Bashir's best friend.

09:34.870 --> 09:37.009
Do you know where
we could find him?

09:37.040 --> 09:38.962
He runs a flower shop.

09:39.010 --> 09:41.808
Ijust talked to him.

09:41.840 --> 09:44.968
He's going to do the flowers
for Bashir's funeral.

09:51.720 --> 09:53.256
Moshin Aziz?
That's right.

09:53.290 --> 09:56.088
We'd like to ask you a few
questions about Bashir Sajadi.

09:56.120 --> 09:57.656
MO:
Have they found out who did it?

09:57.690 --> 09:59.282
AL:
No, not yet.

09:59.330 --> 10:02.663
MO: I told Bashir driving a cab
is too dangerous.

10:02.700 --> 10:03.860
He was robbed already twice.

10:03.900 --> 10:04.992
Did his wife tell you?

10:05.030 --> 10:06.258
We don't think
this was a robbery.

10:06.300 --> 10:07.369
What are you talking about?

10:07.400 --> 10:09.766
Mo, right?
You mind ifI call you Mo?

10:09.810 --> 10:11.129
Sure.

10:11.170 --> 10:12.933
555-1246-- that
your cell phone number?

10:12.980 --> 10:15.699
Yes. Why are you asking me this?

10:15.740 --> 10:18.049
You called Bashir
the afternoon he was murdered.

10:18.080 --> 10:19.718
Yes, I called him.
AL:
Thing is,

10:19.750 --> 10:22.275
we tried to find the records
for that phone, only the number

10:22.320 --> 10:23.787
wasn't traceable--
there a reason for that?

10:23.820 --> 10:25.378
Untraceable? No.

10:25.420 --> 10:27.012
No, I just don't want to pay

10:27.060 --> 10:28.379
for an expensive
cell phone plan.

10:28.420 --> 10:29.956
I pay in cash.

10:29.990 --> 10:32.220
Look-- here's my phone;
I have nothing to hide.

10:32.260 --> 10:33.955
Why did you call him?

10:34.000 --> 10:36.252
To see if he wanted to watch
a football game with me.

10:36.300 --> 10:39.224
Football? There's no football
in the summertime, Mr. Aziz.

10:39.270 --> 10:41.261
I mean soccer. There was
a game in Prospect Park.

10:41.300 --> 10:43.131
It's not a crime
to like soccer, is it?

10:43.170 --> 10:45.229
Well, that depends
on who you're talking to.

10:45.270 --> 10:47.670
I got nothing against soccer;
I just prefer football.

10:48.980 --> 10:50.402
Listen, Mo,
you may have been

10:50.450 --> 10:51.940
talking to Bashir when

10:51.980 --> 10:54.312
his killer or killers
were in the car with him.

10:54.350 --> 10:56.215
What?
Did he say anything to you

10:56.250 --> 10:58.741
about his passengers,
anything at all?

10:58.790 --> 11:00.212
Oh, my God.

11:00.260 --> 11:01.215
What?

11:01.260 --> 11:03.080
When I talked to
Bashir that day,

11:03.130 --> 11:05.223
someone was speaking
Pashto to him.

11:05.260 --> 11:06.693
Did you hear what was said?

11:06.730 --> 11:08.823
Uh, only a few words.

11:08.860 --> 11:11.897
But it was a man and it
was definitely Pashto.

11:11.930 --> 11:14.865
The passenger's fluency
in Pashto probably means

11:14.900 --> 11:17.232
the assailant or assailants_come
from either of these regions

11:17.270 --> 11:18.430
in Afghanistan or Pakistan.

11:18.470 --> 11:21.177
Which matches the
ethnic background

11:21.210 --> 11:23.098
of our two terrorism suspects.

11:25.350 --> 11:27.341
Okay.

11:27.380 --> 11:28.916
Where's all this
coming from, Burns?

11:28.950 --> 11:30.087
Sorry?

11:30.120 --> 11:31.849
It's just, I can't imagine

11:31.890 --> 11:33.414
the 117th in Queens

11:33.460 --> 11:35.314
required any kind of

11:35.360 --> 11:36.418
geo-political expertise.

11:36.460 --> 11:38.155
Oh, you'd be surprised.

11:40.530 --> 11:43.124
Okay, the problem is,

11:43.170 --> 11:45.263
according to the task force's
surveillance reports,

11:45.300 --> 11:48.360
we can't definitively place
their terrorist suspects

11:48.400 --> 11:50.061
at our murder scene.
But nothing says
they weren't there.

11:50.110 --> 11:51.759
The task force
lost track of them

11:51.810 --> 11:52.834
for three hours
that afternoon.

11:52.880 --> 11:54.177
That's not enough.

11:54.210 --> 11:55.108
And you already have motive.

11:55.140 --> 11:57.108
Sajadi was helping
to set these guys up.

11:57.150 --> 11:59.300
Al, I understand you want
to go get these guys.

11:59.350 --> 12:01.079
Id... I don't think
we're there.

12:01.120 --> 12:02.314
Okay, you don't think so

12:02.350 --> 12:03.749
or your task force buddies
don't think so?

12:03.790 --> 12:06.850
I don't think I like
what you're implying.

12:06.890 --> 12:08.152
Then I won't imply it,
I'll just say it straight up.

12:08.190 --> 12:10.226
JTF wants to keep these
guys on the street,

12:10.260 --> 12:11.420
so they can make
their weapons sting.

12:11.460 --> 12:12.688
Which makes sense, they've been
building it for six months.

12:12.730 --> 12:16.188
And my guess is, they don't give
two cents about a dead cabbie.

12:16.230 --> 12:18.266
Even one who may have died
trying to help them.

12:18.300 --> 12:20.393
Oh, please,
it is not that simple.

12:20.440 --> 12:22.032
What is simple is I got
a murder investigation,

12:22.070 --> 12:23.469
and I got two suspects
I want to talk to.

12:23.510 --> 12:24.534
Fine!

12:24.570 --> 12:25.764
I'll see what I can do.

12:25.810 --> 12:26.799
Not good enough.

12:26.840 --> 12:28.330
Excuse me?
When you hired me,

12:28.380 --> 12:29.972
the deal was I make
the tactical calls

12:30.010 --> 12:31.272
and you back me up.

12:31.310 --> 12:33.175
I'm making this call.

12:33.220 --> 12:35.074
Now it's your turn.

12:35.120 --> 12:37.418
Okay.

12:37.450 --> 12:39.247
Okay...

12:39.290 --> 12:40.518
but the terrorism guys
are gonna want

12:40.560 --> 12:41.879
to make the collar.

12:41.920 --> 12:44.753
I'm fine with that.

12:47.360 --> 12:49.294
Baku, by the way.

12:51.430 --> 12:53.534
Live feed incoming.

12:53.570 --> 12:56.869
They got them up in the Bronx.

12:56.910 --> 12:58.559
How did you get Eliot
to agree to this?

12:58.610 --> 13:00.339
I believe you've experienced
my powers of persuasion.

13:00.380 --> 13:02.029
Oh, so you plowed him
with mai tais?

13:02.080 --> 13:04.776
What? That's not how I...

13:06.250 --> 13:08.377
What, you got something?
OFFICER: Get out of the car!

13:08.420 --> 13:11.139
Lift your shirt! Turn around!

13:12.860 --> 13:15.215
On your knees! Get down!

13:15.260 --> 13:16.352
OFFICER:
Hands behind your head!

13:21.330 --> 13:24.367
I need to talk to Webster.

13:26.170 --> 13:27.239
CARRIE:
Ooh.

13:27.270 --> 13:30.103
I see you're settling in.

13:30.140 --> 13:32.404
Seems like I never left
these burial grounds.

13:32.440 --> 13:33.475
Well, you're glowing.

13:33.510 --> 13:35.478
Looks like Manhattan
agrees With you.

13:35.510 --> 13:37.546
Oh, yeah, well, it's a whole
different world, you know?

13:37.580 --> 13:39.445
Oh, it is indeed.

13:39.480 --> 13:42.017
The Manhattan dead are a much
better class of cadaver.

13:42.050 --> 13:44.541
I just autopsied
a hedge fund manager,

13:44.590 --> 13:47.479
and his arteries still
reeked of porterhouse.

13:47.520 --> 13:49.351
So, I'm here

13:49.390 --> 13:51.551
about the cab driver, Sajadi.

13:51.590 --> 13:52.989
Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah, okay.

13:54.130 --> 13:55.449
Okay.

13:55.500 --> 13:57.263
The bullet_was from
a nine-millimeter.

13:57.300 --> 13:59.120
The projectile entered and hit

13:59.170 --> 14:01.138
the spinal column
and fragmented.

14:01.170 --> 14:04.003
I noted a slight
downward trajectory.

14:04.040 --> 14:06.031
There were
no defen5ive wounds,

14:06.070 --> 14:07.901
uh, which means
he either knew his killer

14:07.940 --> 14:09.532
and exited the
cab voluntarily,

