right in the cab.
So you're saying

15:25.390 --> 15:27.381
the killer had some sort
of military training?

15:27.420 --> 15:30.059
I'm saying whoever it is

15:30.090 --> 15:32.456
knew enough to have Sajadi
lift his shirt

15:32.490 --> 15:34.526
so they could check him
for explosives.

15:36.430 --> 15:38.523
I think our guy's a soldier.

15:47.310 --> 15:48.709
A soldier?
Well, according
to Carrie's theory,

15:48.740 --> 15:50.674
whoever killed Bashir Sajadi
put him on his knees

15:50.710 --> 15:52.109
with his hands on his head,

15:52.150 --> 15:53.412
which is why,
when he was shot...

15:54.720 --> 15:57.188
...he couldn't reflexively
brace his fall.

15:57.220 --> 15:59.643
Interesting theory, but at
this point, it's just a cartoon.

15:59.690 --> 16:01.157
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

16:01.190 --> 16:03.488
No, a cartoon is a series
of drawings, my friend.

16:03.530 --> 16:05.122
This is
a computer-generated,

16:05.160 --> 16:06.582
digital-sequenced animation.

16:06.630 --> 16:08.257
You really
can't compare the two.

16:08.300 --> 16:11.326
Like comparing Pinocchio
to, say, X-Men.

16:11.370 --> 16:13.998
Exactly. All right,
so can I proceed?

16:14.040 --> 16:16.258
Please.
Okay. So I talked
to an Army attach

16:16.300 --> 16:18.006
and described
the arrest protocol.

16:18.040 --> 16:20.008
He said the American military
trains its personnel

16:20.040 --> 16:22.270
out in the field to place
a captive on their knees,

16:22.310 --> 16:23.777
with their hands clasped
on their head.

16:23.810 --> 16:26.142
And to have prisoners

16:26.180 --> 16:28.148
lift their shirts to_s_ee if
