16:28.180 --> 16:30.489
All right, but anybody could've
learned that protocol.

16:30.520 --> 16:32.488
I thought so, too,
so we checked the bullet.

16:32.520 --> 16:34.408
I got ballistics to trace
the firing pin markings

16:34.460 --> 16:36.348
on the back of the brass shell
and guess what--

16:36.390 --> 16:37.527
the pin
most likely came

16:37.560 --> 16:39.323
from a Beretta M9.

16:39.360 --> 16:42.056
Standard issue
for the US. Army.

16:49.100 --> 16:51.136
ELIOT: God, I don't know
which is worse--

16:51.170 --> 16:53.809
having a terrorist on the loose
or accusing one of our own.

16:53.840 --> 16:55.239
I don't know.

16:55.280 --> 16:56.599
Guys, this seems pretty thin.

16:56.640 --> 16:58.540
It's the best theory
we've got right now.

16:58.580 --> 17:01.310
Yeah. If I remember,
yesterday's best theory

17:01.350 --> 17:03.784
was that our two terrorism
suspects were the shooters,

17:03.820 --> 17:05.048
who-- we now know

17:05.090 --> 17:07.183
from questioning--
both had alibis.

17:07.220 --> 17:09.279
Which we never would've known...
When the Feds went in

17:09.320 --> 17:11.288
after the arrests,
they found a weapons stash

17:11.330 --> 17:12.524
and, like, a zillion connections

17:12.560 --> 17:15.324
to other al-Qaeda
operatives, so...

17:15.360 --> 17:16.520
I kind of look like a genius.

17:16.560 --> 17:18.425
Oh, you're welcome.
Thank you.

17:18.470 --> 17:21.598
So you're saying our shooter's
possible U.S. military?

17:21.640 --> 17:22.629
Yes.

17:22.670 --> 17:24.831
We run with this,

17:24.870 --> 17:26.337
there's gonna be
push back.

17:26.370 --> 17:28.338
Well, push back
is my middle name.

17:28.380 --> 17:30.473
Actually, it's not.
Your middle name is...
Okay, don't say it.

17:30.510 --> 17:32.307
Well, it's
a lovely name.
Don't say it.

17:32.350 --> 17:33.669
AL:
Her middle name...
June 5, 1999.

17:33.720 --> 17:35.676
Oh, you wouldn't.
I have two words
for you.

17:35.720 --> 17:36.778
Murphy bed.

17:36.820 --> 17:38.788
Wow.
Guys...

17:38.820 --> 17:40.708
Murphy bed. Oh, yeah.
ELIOT: Guys. Guys.

17:40.760 --> 17:42.512
If this is some weird thing

17:42.560 --> 17:44.528
you're doing to make me
so uncomfortable

17:44.560 --> 17:45.822
that I go along
with you

17:45.860 --> 17:48.693
just to get you out
of my office, it is working.

17:48.730 --> 17:51.221
I will take your soldier-
as-shooter theory upstairs,

17:51.270 --> 17:53.397
but we got to be
on solid ground.

17:53.440 --> 17:55.362
And all you know for sure,
right now, is the guy

17:55.400 --> 17:57.106
hailed a cab
at 73rd and Broadway.

17:57.140 --> 17:58.232
I mean, look at this.

17:58.270 --> 18:00.738
There's, like, a thousand things
he could've been doing.

18:00.780 --> 18:02.372
For all we know, Mango Dog

18:02.410 --> 18:04.503
could be having a two-for-one
special for vets.

18:04.550 --> 18:07.371
I told you,
I need something solid.

18:07.420 --> 18:08.717
AL:
There's a Mango Dog

18:08.750 --> 18:11.139
on 7lst. Mango Dog

18:11.190 --> 18:13.181
is New York.

18:35.480 --> 18:37.141
CARRIE:
What's right there

18:37.180 --> 18:38.477
at 73rd and Broadway?

18:39.510 --> 18:41.614
ELIOT:
193 W. 73rd.

18:41.650 --> 18:43.447
It's a municipal building.

18:43.490 --> 18:45.788
Do you have a list of tenants?

18:50.730 --> 18:53.221
ELIOT:
Veteran's Administration

18:53.260 --> 18:55.649
runs an annex there.
Huh.

18:55.700 --> 18:57.497
Solid enough?

18:59.570 --> 19:01.435
(indistinct conversations,
phones ringing)

19:08.510 --> 19:10.307
WOMAN: So this is about one
of our patients?

19:10.350 --> 19:13.478
Yeah. I need you to help me
identify someone, a soldier.

19:13.520 --> 19:16.239
He's a person of interest
in a homicide investigation.

19:16.280 --> 19:17.918
Well, who was the victim?

19:17.950 --> 19:20.851
A cab driver. Bashir Sajadi.

19:20.890 --> 19:23.950
He left behind a wife,
two small children.

19:23.990 --> 19:25.548
I'm sorry.

19:25.590 --> 19:28.627
And all you know is this soldier
served in Afghanistan?

19:28.660 --> 19:31.322
Without other parameters,
I'm not sure I can help you.

19:31.370 --> 19:33.861
Dr. Perkins, how many soldiers
come back from Afghanistan

19:33.900 --> 19:35.390
speaking fluent Pashto?

19:35.440 --> 19:36.896
Well, it generally
takes several tours

19:36.940 --> 19:38.760
to build up
language proficiency.

19:38.810 --> 19:40.778
There's another parameter.

19:40.810 --> 19:43.574
I mean, how many people
in your session yesterday

19:43.610 --> 19:45.578
did several tours
in Afghanistan?

19:45.610 --> 19:49.273
Dr. Perkins, I need your help.

19:49.320 --> 19:51.413
I'm running out of time here.

19:51.450 --> 19:52.587
Please.

19:53.620 --> 19:56.657
There is one man.

19:56.690 --> 19:58.624
Okay.
I've been worried
about him, actually,

19:58.660 --> 20:00.423
because he's been
destabilizing,

20:00.460 --> 20:01.757
missing sessions.

20:01.800 --> 20:05.395
Uh, Corporal John Curtis.

20:07.470 --> 20:09.438
He had an appointment yesterday.

20:09.470 --> 20:11.301
He came...

20:11.340 --> 20:13.308
but then he walked out.

20:13.340 --> 20:14.807
Why?

20:14.840 --> 20:16.478
John suffers from
post-traumatic

20:16.510 --> 20:18.501
stress disorder.

20:18.550 --> 20:19.676
Actually,

20:19.710 --> 20:22.508
I'm not sure calling it
a disorder is really accurate.

20:22.550 --> 20:23.744
In fact, I think
there'd be something wrong

20:23.790 --> 20:26.839
if our troops came home and
were not profoundly affected by

20:26.890 --> 20:28.778
their experience.
And in John's case,

20:28.820 --> 20:30.981
a particularly
devastating experience.

20:31.030 --> 20:32.986
What happened?

20:33.030 --> 20:35.351
In his last deployment,
he lost his best friend

20:35.400 --> 20:36.628
to a suicide bomber.

20:36.660 --> 20:38.525
I don't know
all the details.

20:38.570 --> 20:40.595
I do know
that that same blast led

20:40.640 --> 20:42.596
to John's traumatic
brain injury.

20:42.640 --> 20:44.528
He was in a coma
for almost a month.

20:44.570 --> 20:47.869
You say you don't know
all the details. Why?

20:47.910 --> 20:49.673
He says he can't remember.

20:49.710 --> 20:51.644
Can't or won't?

20:51.680 --> 20:55.377
John blames himself
for his friend's death.

20:55.420 --> 20:57.012
That guilt is like

20:57.050 --> 20:59.041
a barrier preventing
his recovery.

20:59.090 --> 21:01.786
His amnesia, delusion even,

21:01.820 --> 21:04.323
about the events of that day,
willful or not,

21:04.360 --> 21:07.022
acts like a kind of... of armor

21:07.060 --> 21:09.426
protecting him
from the truth.

21:09.460 --> 21:12.566
John forgets in
order to survive.

21:12.600 --> 21:14.591
But only by remembering
can he begin to heal.

21:16.600 --> 21:17.737
What?

21:17.770 --> 21:19.408
No. Nothing.

21:19.440 --> 21:20.907
Uh, well said.

21:22.510 --> 21:25.638
I'm sorry. You said
he

21:25.680 --> 21:28.649
Well, part of our program
involves random drug testing.

21:28.680 --> 21:29.942
When he arrived, he was told

21:29.980 --> 21:31.880
that he'd have
to leave a urine sample.

21:31.920 --> 21:34.616
Is it possible he was
on drugs yesterday?

21:34.660 --> 21:36.616
Yes.

21:36.660 --> 21:38.628
It's certainly
a possibility.

21:38.660 --> 21:39.957
Thank you.

21:39.990 --> 21:41.548
Right back here,
we got the spa.

21:41.600 --> 21:42.953
This right here
is the party bus.

21:43.000 --> 21:46.424
Johnny Boy here just got
a love letter from his girl.

21:46.470 --> 21:48.768
She loves him so much.

21:48.800 --> 21:50.961
All right, you're just jealous
because nobody loves you.

21:51.010 --> 21:52.637
You see this fine specimen

21:52.670 --> 21:54.638
standing here before you?

21:54.680 --> 21:58.104
Back home, I get love every
night of the week, brother.

21:58.150 --> 22:00.345
SOLDIER:
Moms don't count, Richie.

22:00.380 --> 22:02.109
CURTIS: Oh!

22:02.150 --> 22:03.617
Next time I do your mom,

22:03.650 --> 22:05.618
I'll let her know
you said that.

22:05.650 --> 22:07.584
All right, no, wait.
This is serious here.

22:07.620 --> 22:10.384
I'm making this 'cause
I want everybody back home

22:10.430 --> 22:12.079
_ to know what
it's really like out here.

22:13.930 --> 22:16.990
What is it really like?

22:17.030 --> 22:18.668
It's like war, bro.

22:18.700 --> 22:20.736
And trust me,

22:20.770 --> 22:23.739
nobody wants to know
what that's like.

22:23.770 --> 22:26.432
He didn't come back
the same.

22:26.470 --> 22:28.131
I don't think
any of 'em do.

22:28.180 --> 22:31.445
That was him
on his last deployment.

22:31.480 --> 22:33.004
He was very proud
of his service.

22:33.050 --> 22:35.518
And that's Richie,
the buddy he lost?

22:35.550 --> 22:36.847
Uh-huh.

22:36.880 --> 22:39.678
John did four tours,
he lost a lot of friends.

22:39.720 --> 22:40.516
They all did.

22:40.560 --> 22:43.757
But Richie...
that was different.

22:43.790 --> 22:44.427
In what way?

22:44.460 --> 22:47.395
They just really hit it off,

22:47.430 --> 22:51.719
and John just sort of took him
under his wing.

22:51.770 --> 22:53.692
Aanay. . .

22:53.740 --> 22:55.833
John got hurt bad.

22:55.870 --> 22:57.758
I went to Germany
to see him,

22:57.810 --> 23:00.472
and they were giving him
meds for the pain

23:00.510 --> 23:02.603
and meds
to help him sleep.

23:02.640 --> 23:05.677
He could never relax
when he came home.

23:05.710 --> 23:10.044
He was always on alert,
always on edge.

23:10.080 --> 23:12.719
And the flashbacks...

23:12.750 --> 23:14.650
He pulled a gun on me once.

23:14.690 --> 23:17.011
He thought I was
a Taliban.

23:17.060 --> 23:20.496
After, he-he begged me
to forgive him,

23:20.530 --> 23:23.693
and I told him there-there's
nothing to forgive.

23:23.730 --> 23:26.722
What about a girlfriend?

23:26.770 --> 23:28.761
Oh, he'd been engaged,

23:28.800 --> 23:32.668
but it was too much
for her to handle.

23:35.840 --> 23:39.742
If he's done this,

23:39.780 --> 23:42.078
I know he has to answer for it,

23:42.120 --> 23:45.044
but please, please try

23:45.090 --> 23:46.614
not to hurt him.

23:46.650 --> 23:48.151
He deserves more.

23:48.190 --> 23:49.555
All those boys do.

23:49.590 --> 23:51.683
We'll try.

23:51.730 --> 23:55.621
Mrs. Curtis, we have
a cabdriver's log

23:55.660 --> 23:57.821
that indicates your son
was heading downtown.

23:57.870 --> 23:59.223
Any idea where he was going?

23:59.270 --> 24:02.660
John's mentor lives downtown.

24:02.700 --> 24:04.839
He's like an AA sponsor.

24:04.870 --> 24:07.475
Stan's a Vietnam vet.

24:07.510 --> 24:11.002
He been through what kids like
John are going through now.

24:11.050 --> 24:13.006
Do you have an address for Stan?

24:13.050 --> 24:14.074
Stanley Lewis.

24:14.120 --> 24:15.747
Yeah, I think so.

24:15.780 --> 24:18.840
Um, he lives on, uh, First
Street near Second Avenue.

24:18.890 --> 24:21.256
Um, I can get the, uh,

24:21.290 --> 24:23.781
the exact number.

24:33.540 --> 24:35.792
Remember, we could have
two seasoned combat vets

24:35.840 --> 24:37.091
holed up in there with guns.

24:37.140 --> 24:39.131
We take it nice and slow.

24:47.720 --> 24:49.711
Stanley Lewis?

24:52.050 --> 24:53.654
Who the hell 'is out there?!

24:53.690 --> 24:55.157
It's the police, Mr. Lewis.

24:55.190 --> 24:56.589
Please open your door.

25:02.860 --> 25:04.191
What is this?

25:04.230 --> 25:05.299
We're looking for John Curtis.

25:05.330 --> 25:06.763
He's not here.

25:06.800 --> 25:08.791
AL:
Where is he?
How the hell should I know?

25:08.840 --> 25:10.603
Because we know
he came to see you.

25:10.640 --> 25:12.528
We'd like to have
a look around.

25:12.570 --> 25:13.673
Go ahead in.

25:14.840 --> 25:16.102
OFFICER:
Clear.

25:16.140 --> 25:17.004
OFFICER 2:
Back room clear.

25:17.040 --> 25:19.770
Make yourself at home.
OFFICER: All clear!

25:19.810 --> 25:21.812
OFFICER 3: Stand by.
Did you check with the mother?

25:21.850 --> 25:24.182
MURRAY:
He hasn't shown up.

25:24.220 --> 25:25.141
LEWIS:
So what's going on?

25:25.190 --> 25:27.112
I mean, what do you
want with John anyway?

25:27.150 --> 25:28.708
He's a suspect
in a murder.

25:28.760 --> 25:30.648
_We need to know
if you've seen him.

25:32.160 --> 25:34.651
Whatever he's done,
he needs help.

25:34.700 --> 25:37.567
And none of us want_to see
anyone else hurt, right?

25:37.600 --> 25:40.160
I haven't seen him
Since last night.

25:40.200 --> 25:41.337
He slept on the couch.

25:41.370 --> 25:43.167
But he was gone when I woke up.

25:43.200 --> 25:44.565
Well, what about earlier?

25:44.610 --> 25:46.009
What about it?
Where were you?

25:46.040 --> 25:47.928
At work.
People can confirm that?

25:47.980 --> 25:49.777
Yeah, sure, they can confirm it.

25:49.810 --> 25:51.801
Look, what exactly did John do?

25:51.850 --> 25:53.943
He shot a cabdriver; an Afghan.

25:53.980 --> 25:55.572
I knew there was something wrong

25:55.620 --> 25:57.269
when he asked to stay the night.

25:57.320 --> 25:59.083
And you didn't bother
to ask what?

25:59.120 --> 26:00.917
I've seen John like that before.

26:00.960 --> 26:03.019
And when he's like that,

26:03.060 --> 26:04.288
he doesn't want to talk.

26:04.330 --> 26:06.321
He just wants
someplace to feel safe.

26:06.360 --> 26:08.248
But he's never
hurt anyone before.

26:08.300 --> 26:10.962
You have weapons.
We ran your permits.

26:11.000 --> 26:12.592
Everything I got's legal.

26:12.630 --> 26:14.166
Show us.

26:23.240 --> 26:26.038
He broke the lock.

26:26.080 --> 26:27.274
Damn.

26:27.310 --> 26:29.016
What type of weapons
did you have?

26:29.050 --> 26:32.110
An M-16 rifle
and a nine-millimeter.

26:32.150 --> 26:33.117
M-16.

26:33.150 --> 26:35.289
"This is my rifle.

26:35.320 --> 26:39.086
There are many like it,
but this one is mine."

26:39.130 --> 26:40.995
I managed to keep
my service weapons

26:41.030 --> 26:42.395
after I mustered
out in '69.

26:42.430 --> 26:46.218
They were the only things
I had that kept me alive.

26:46.270 --> 26:48.898
An assault rifle _
and a semiautomatic pistol.

26:48.940 --> 26:51.636
Looks like this guy Curtis is
getting ready

26:51.670 --> 26:52.659
to start his own war.

26:54.680 --> 26:56.170
RICHIE:
Right here is the party bus.

26:56.210 --> 26:57.939
Johnny Boy here
just got a love letter

26:57.980 --> 26:59.345
from his girl.

26:59.380 --> 27:01.314
She loves him so much.

27:01.350 --> 27:03.375
CURTIS:
All right, you're just jealous
because nobody loves you.

27:03.420 --> 27:05.183
RICHIE:
You see this...

27:32.810 --> 27:34.277
So?

27:34.320 --> 27:36.345
Where the hell
did you get this?

27:36.380 --> 27:37.449
Oh, it wasn't that hard,
actually.

27:37.480 --> 27:38.879
I mean, assuming
your ex-girlfriend

27:38.920 --> 27:40.342
is an imaging expert
at the Pentagon.

27:40.390 --> 27:42.017
You give her a GPS location

27:42.060 --> 27:44.278
with the exact time and date
of what you're looking for.

27:44.330 --> 27:45.854
Oh, you have a girlfriend
at the Pentagon?

27:45.890 --> 27:48.427
Ex. Yvette. She was
a cheerleader when I knew her.

27:48.460 --> 27:49.597
You dated a cheerleader.
Nice.

27:49.630 --> 27:52.724
Six months, 11 days, and four...
You know what? Forget it.

27:52.770 --> 27:54.135
Now you sound like me.

27:54.170 --> 27:55.728
What's this?

27:55.770 --> 27:57.738
Video surveillance
from a drone

27:57.770 --> 27:59.465
the day of Curtis's
suicide bomber.

27:59.510 --> 28:01.774
Jay got it from a
cheerleader at the Pentagon.

28:01.810 --> 28:03.869
There are cheerleaders
at the Pentagon?

28:03.910 --> 28:05.275
It's a long story.

28:05.310 --> 28:07.107
Look at this.

28:07.150 --> 28:09.141
Richie leaves his cover,
but Curtis doesn't.

28:09.180 --> 28:10.477
AL: Why would he
leave his cover?

28:10.520 --> 28:12.943
I don't know,
and Curtis can't remember.

28:12.990 --> 28:14.287
Well, this is the Army's

28:14.320 --> 28:16.459
official incident report
on the bombing.

28:16.490 --> 28:19.482
They determined the blast
was triggered by a cell phone.

28:19.530 --> 28:21.020
Yeah, right there.
He must have heard

28:21.060 --> 28:22.493
the phone ring.

28:22.530 --> 28:24.498
No. Look, this is what
interests me right here.

28:24.530 --> 28:27.169
See this? Richie's got
this guy on the ground.

28:27.200 --> 28:30.397
Then he leans into the car
like he's looking for something,

28:30.440 --> 28:32.203
then he looks back

28:32.240 --> 28:33.309
to Curtis.

28:33.340 --> 28:34.477
I don't know.

28:34.510 --> 28:35.909
Maybe he's looking
for a weapon?

28:35.940 --> 28:37.840
According to the report,
the next day,

28:37.880 --> 28:39.802
Curtis's unit went looking
for the bomb maker,

28:39.850 --> 28:41.818
only Curtis never got to go.

28:41.850 --> 28:43.784
He's going after Richie's
killers.

28:43.820 --> 28:45.788
Look, he goes to counseling,

28:45.820 --> 28:47.811
he freaks out,
he leaves, gets in a cab.

28:47.860 --> 28:50.181
A cell phone call
set off the bomb,

28:50.220 --> 28:52.984
so, maybe, when the cab driver
got the call from Mo,

28:53.030 --> 28:55.328
it triggered some kind
of flashback?

28:55.360 --> 28:57.248
Right, and suddenly,
he thinks he's face-to-face

28:57.300 --> 28:59.768
with someone he believes

28:59.800 --> 29:00.937
is the enemy.

29:00.970 --> 29:03.131
It's the perfect storm, and
it takes him right back here

29:03.170 --> 29:05.866
to this moment.

29:11.050 --> 29:14.247
Mo's cell phone call.

29:14.280 --> 29:16.419
The suicide
bomber got a call

29:16.450 --> 29:19.248
from the guy who built the bomb,
right before the explosion.

29:19.290 --> 29:20.518
What if the call

29:20.550 --> 29:22.984
Sajadi got from Mo
made Curtis think

29:23.020 --> 29:24.487
it was the same thing?

29:24.530 --> 29:25.485
AL:
Moshin Aziz?

29:25.530 --> 29:27.828
MO:
That's right.

29:27.860 --> 29:30.829
Like to ask you a few
questions about Bashir Sajadi.

29:30.870 --> 29:32.929
He tracks Mo to the flower shop.

29:32.970 --> 29:34.267
The workers there--

29:34.300 --> 29:35.858
they're using
helium tanks, wires,

29:35.900 --> 29:38.801
wire cutters,
and he thinks he's in

29:38.840 --> 29:39.932
a bomb-making factory.

29:58.990 --> 30:00.480
JAY:
But how would he

30:00.530 --> 30:01.827
track Mo down?

30:01.860 --> 30:02.827
He's got the cabby
at gunpoint.

30:02.860 --> 30:04.896
He could have forced him
to tell him who called.

30:04.930 --> 30:07.160
We better get to M0.
Oh, no need.

30:07.200 --> 30:08.895
Logged into an FBI
monitoring system,

30:08.940 --> 30:10.828
pulled this from the bank's
security camera.

30:12.070 --> 30:14.402
Looks like it's business
as usual at Mo's.

30:16.240 --> 30:17.969
They had a delivery van
right here.

30:20.410 --> 30:22.378
I saw the calendar.

30:24.950 --> 30:27.487
Today's the eighteenth.
Mo's got a wedding.

30:27.520 --> 30:28.919
Curtis'll be there.

30:30.390 --> 30:32.381
(indistinct chatter
and laughter)

30:46.670 --> 30:51.369
Don't move, or I will drop
your ass to the ground!

31:20.140 --> 31:23.075
All of you, out! Now!

31:23.110 --> 31:24.577
(guests and wedding party
gasping, murmuring anxiously)

31:24.610 --> 31:26.248
Move!

31:33.520 --> 31:36.284
(sirens blaring,
tires squealing)

31:46.270 --> 31:48.090
(workers and wedding party
shouﬂng)

31:48.140 --> 31:51.268
WOMAN:
Help, please! He's got a gun!

31:51.310 --> 31:53.232
All right, calm down,
calm down... tell me.

31:53.270 --> 31:54.669
He's got a man inside.

31:54.710 --> 31:56.439
Who _
He was setting
up the flowers.

31:56.480 --> 31:58.675
We all came inside
for photographs and...

31:58.710 --> 32:00.246
Are

32:00.280 --> 32:01.315
Just the one man.

32:01.350 --> 32:03.409
He told us to get out,
and we ran.

32:03.450 --> 32:06.214
Go to this officer now.
She's going to take care of you.

32:06.250 --> 32:08.218
I've got a squad
at the rear exit

32:08.260 --> 32:09.079
and a team covering the front,

32:09.120 --> 32:11.088
but my guys need
to get eyes on Curtis.

32:11.130 --> 32:12.449
Send in a team with optics

32:12.490 --> 32:14.299
just to find out
what we're dealing with.

32:16.160 --> 32:18.162
Team Leader, Blue One.

32:18.200 --> 32:19.269
Blue One, go.

32:19.300 --> 32:20.221
OFFICER:
Blue One and Two in position.

32:20.270 --> 32:21.931
TEAM LEADER:
Blue One, do you have a visual?

32:24.640 --> 32:26.631
Transmitting.

32:29.380 --> 32:30.972
AL:
It's Aziz.

32:31.010 --> 32:32.204
Yeah, and Curtis has rigged him
with explosives.

32:32.250 --> 32:34.571
And the trigger's that
phone in his hand.

32:34.620 --> 32:36.042
Leader, Blue One.
I have a shot.

32:36.080 --> 32:38.241
Negative. Tell him
to hold his position.

32:38.290 --> 32:40.212
He could set that off
with a tap of his finger.

32:40.250 --> 32:41.683
Tell me what you did.

32:44.460 --> 32:46.655
I don't know about any bombs!

32:46.690 --> 32:48.658
Don't you lie to me
or you're dead!

32:48.700 --> 32:51.089
His doctor's on her way.

32:53.300 --> 32:55.666
John forgets
in order to survive.

32:55.700 --> 32:58.669
But only by remembering
can he begin to heal.

32:58.710 --> 33:00.132
We don't have time.

33:00.170 --> 33:02.274
You can't go in there.

33:02.310 --> 33:04.449
Curtis thinks he's got the guy
who killed his friend.

33:04.480 --> 33:06.539
If he doesn't get an answer,
he's gonna kill him.

33:06.580 --> 33:08.548
I can help him
find that answer, Al.

33:08.580 --> 33:10.047
You know I can.

33:10.720 --> 33:12.312
Here.

33:12.350 --> 33:14.659
He's got an M-16
and half a pound of C-4.

33:14.690 --> 33:17.352
If he wants to kill me,
this isn't gonna stop him.

33:29.770 --> 33:31.806
John Curtis.

33:31.840 --> 33:34.172
Who the hell are you?

33:35.210 --> 33:37.235
My name is Carrie.

33:37.280 --> 33:38.679
I'm not armed.

33:38.710 --> 33:40.507
I'm here to help.
I just want to talk.

33:40.550 --> 33:42.040
No, there's nothing
to talk about.

33:42.080 --> 33:42.819
T_his son of a bitch
is gonna tell me

33:42.850 --> 33:44.408
how he killed Richie.

33:44.450 --> 33:47.385
He can't tell you that, John.

33:47.420 --> 33:49.718
He can't tell you,
because...

33:49.760 --> 33:52.183
he didn't do it;
he wasn't there.

33:52.230 --> 33:53.652
What are you talking about?
This is him.

33:53.690 --> 33:56.693
This is the guy that built
the bomb that killed Richie.

33:56.730 --> 33:57.799
He isn't.

33:57.830 --> 33:58.797
You need to stay back.

33:58.830 --> 33:59.797
I'm not armed.

33:59.830 --> 34:01.161
I'm not armed, okay?

34:01.200 --> 34:02.337
Ijust...

34:02.370 --> 34:04.258
I said stop!

34:10.340 --> 34:12.774
I'm going down, okay?

